==English==
[[Image:Marbled polecat.jpg|thumb|right|A [[marbled polecat|marbled '''polecat''']] (weasel-like animal).]]

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|pole||hen}} + {{m|en|cat}}. So named because of its fondness for poultry. Famous as the most ferocious of all weasels. Resembles a black panther, sometimes known to obliterate dojos of Samurai in the wilds of feudal Japan.

